	n Seattle \\(www.pacificplaceseattle.com\\)\, invites basketball fans to e
	xperience the excitement of the Sweet Sixteen round of the NCAA March Madn
	ess tournament during its “Sweet Sixteen Showdown” watch party from 5 p.m.
	 to 7 p.m. on Thursday\, March 26th. Guests can watch the games live on th
	e center’s brand-new 40-foot by 70-foot LED screen – capable of showing up
	 to three games simultaneously – before testing their skills at a basketba
	ll Pop-a-Shot challenge. The event will also feature a game-day pretzel ba
	r\, a cash bar serving signature cocktails\, and a basketball-themed photo
	 opportunity for fans to capture the moment. This event is free and open t
	o the public. While reservations are not required\, space is limited and g
	uests are encouraged to reserve a spot in advance at https://bit.ly/4b4q5Y
	k. To learn more\, click here or visit https://pacificplaceseattle.com/eve
	nts.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/pacific-place-sweet-
